       fhir:index 0 ;
       fhir:Extension.url [ fhir:value "http://hl7.org/fhir/uv/cpg/StructureDefinition/cpg-rationale" ] ;
       fhir:Extension.valueMarkdown [ fhir:value "In countries with low levels of measles transmission, administration of MCV2 at 15-18 months of age ensures early \nprotection of the individual. The minimum interval between MCV1 and MCV2 is 4 weeks. As a general rule, live vaccines should \nbe given either simultaneously or at intervals of 4 weeks. An exception to this rule is OPV, which can be given at any time \nbefore or after measles vaccination without interference in the response to either vaccine." ]
